net.zerobandwidth.android.lib.database.querybuilder

Class InsertionBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.zerobandwidth.android.lib.database.querybuilder.QueryBuilder<InsertionBuilder,java.lang.Long>
      • net.zerobandwidth.android.lib.database.querybuilder.InsertionBuilder

  • public class InsertionBuilder
extends QueryBuilder<InsertionBuilder,java.lang.Long>
    Builds a SQLite INSERT query.

    Examples

    Insert a row. 
     long nID = QueryBuilder.insertInto( sTableName )
     .setValues( vals )
     .executeOn( db )
     ;
    Insert a row, specifying that the operation should be rolled back if a conflict arises. 
     long nID = QueryBuilder.insertInto( sTableName )
     .setValues( vals )
     .onConflict( SQLiteDatabase.CONFLICT_ROLLBACK )
     .executeOn( db )
     ;
    Insert a series of rows. 
     Vector vnIDs = new Vector<>() ;
 for( ContentValues vals : aSeveralValues )
 {
     long nID = QueryBuilder.insertInto( sTableName )
         .setValues( vals )
         .executeOn( db )
         ;
     if( nID != SQLitePortal.INSERT_FAILED )
         vnIDs.add(nID) ;
 }
    Since:
    zerobandwidth-net/android 0.1.1 (#20)
    See Also:
    SQLiteDatabase.insertWithOnConflict(String, String, ContentValues, int)
